However I think the reason I enjoy Folklore and Evermore so much, it reminds me of her first album that I would listen to in middle school. Then yesterday when I heard Fearless for the first time ever, THAT is the album to compare New Taylor Swift to the old stuff.

Music is just like medicine, especially with mental health. I remember my team members at a summer job I had would play Reputation on repeat and I would just brush it off and now as I’m listening to it with new ears, this album is the peak of her overall personality.
I always told myself to try new things so I found new musicals to listen to and when that got old, I discovered PATD. I think that’s what made me try Taylor Swift again.

When the year started, I was elated that Selena Gomez released a new album after what seemed like ages. I was also dealing with a lot in January that the album related to so much. Last year, Jonas Brothers got me through camp counseling.

I think this year, everyone on the planet had fallen back on old coping mechanisms. For me specifically, that was Selena Gomez and the Jonas Brothers. In elementary school though, it was Taylor Swift. My brain basically said they made you feel safe when bullied, what’s the diff?

I think the reason artists are doing so much better these days is because they are finally creating THEIR music no matter what they think people will think about it. In the last 2 years of music from people I listened to in middle school, their music has grown exponentially.
